    "schema_version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Country configurations and econometric data. Demo coverage: Ghana (GH), India (IN).",
    "last_updated": "2026-04-25",
    "linkage": {
      "wage_data": "Keys are ISCO-08 4-digit codes; full titles in isco08_taxonomy.json",
      "automation_calibration": "infrastructure_factor multiplies raw scores from frey_osborne.json before reporting",
      "sectors": "Sector slugs are stable and reused across all countries and across wage_data.<isco>.sector"
    },
    "data_sources": [
      "ILOSTAT (sector employment, growth rates)",
      "World Bank WDI (youth unemployment, informality)",
      "Country statistical offices (currency, education taxonomy)",
      "Naukri / GhanaJobs / PLFS (wage estimates, illustrative)"
    ],
    "honesty_note": "Wage and growth figures are plausible composite estimates for hackathon demo. Production replaces these with live ILOSTAT/WDI feeds.",
    "anchoring_note": "Sectors agriculture/services share_employment and growth_annual anchored to World Bank WDI (latest available year, 2024-25) for GH and IN where directly comparable. WDI 'industry' aggregates manufacturing + construction + mining + utilities; finer 7-sector splits (ict, renewable_energy, retail, finance, healthcare, education, construction) are composite estimates. wage_data is composite at ISCO 4-digit; ILOSTAT only publishes wages at ISCO 1-digit major group (see data/raw/ilostat/EAR_4MTH_SEX_OCU_NB_GHA_IND.csv) which doesn't decompose to 4-digit. demographics.youth_unemployment_rate and informality_rate are composite estimates."
  },
